      "title": "Evaluate page: default filter to Pending, move counts into dropdown, persist selection",
      "description": "Three related changes to the feedback filter on the Evaluate page:\n\n1. **Default to Pending:** Change the initial filter value from \"All\" to \"Pending\" so users land on actionable items.\n2. **Move counts into dropdown items:** Remove the (##) count from the page/section title on the left. Instead, each item in the filter dropdown (All, Pending, Mapped, Resolved) should display its own count, e.g. \"Pending (5)\", \"Mapped (3)\".\n3. **Persist selection in localStorage:** Save the user's chosen filter value to `localStorage` (e.g. key `opensprint.evaluateFeedbackFilter`). On page load, read the stored value and apply it; fall back to \"Pending\" if no stored value exists.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- On first visit (no localStorage key), filter defaults to \"Pending\".\n- Each dropdown option shows the count of feedback items matching that status.\n- The title/heading no longer displays a count.\n- Selecting a filter writes the value to localStorage immediately.\n- Refreshing the page restores the previously selected filter.\n- \"All\" option shows the total count across all statuses.",
      "priority": 2,
      "depends_on": []
    }
